<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,258,535]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
In their original description of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Ofwegen &amp; Schleyer (1997)" authorityName=", Ofwegen &amp; Schleyer" authorityYear="1997" box="[540,1016,402,427]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Leptophyton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="benayahui">
<emphasis box="[540,686,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">L. benayahui</emphasis>
, Ofwegen &amp; Schleyer (1997)
</taxonomicName>
state that the sclerites of the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,402,427]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">holotype</typeStatus>
have an eroded appearance, as though the specimen had been stored in formalin. In the newly collected material we have examined this is not the case, and additional details of the distribution and ornamentation of the sclerites can be discerned. Consequently, we update and revise the description of the sclerites of this species.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1114557/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" targetBox="[151,1436,587,1753]" targetPageId="21">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1435,1775,1828]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1775,1797]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">FIGURE 12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Ofwegen &amp; Schleyer" authorityYear="1997" box="[293,532,1775,1797]" class="Anthozoa" family="Nephtheidae" genus="Leptophyton" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="benayahui">
<emphasis box="[293,532,1775,1797]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Leptophyton benayahui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, RMNH Coel. 40209 (SAF333). a, tentacle sclerites; b, sclerites from proximal region of polyps and colony surface; c, sclerites from base of colony.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1867,2036]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="473" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">
The description of the 
<typeStatus box="[455,553,1867,1892]" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">holotype</typeStatus>
states that the polyps lack sclerites, but in the material examined here we find small rods, 
<quantity box="[282,446,1904,1928]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" unit="mm" value="0.06" valueMax="0.08" valueMin="0.04">0.04–0.08 mm</quantity>
long, at the bases of the tentacles (
<figureCitation box="[842,939,1903,1928]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,587,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,587,1753]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Leptophyton benayahui, RMNH Coel.40209 (SAF333). a, tentaclesclerites; b, sclerites from proximal region of polyps and colony surface; c, sclerites from base of colony." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1114557/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Fig. 12a</figureCitation>
). The proximal region of the polyps and the colony surface have spindles, 
<quantity box="[503,670,1940,1964]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" unit="mm" value="0.105" valueMax="0.13" valueMin="0.08">0.08–0.13 mm</quantity>
long, with fairly sparse, high, simple tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[1242,1344,1939,1964]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,587,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,587,1753]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Leptophyton benayahui, RMNH Coel.40209 (SAF333). a, tentaclesclerites; b, sclerites from proximal region of polyps and colony surface; c, sclerites from base of colony." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1114557/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="472">Fig. 12b</figureCitation>
). In the proximal region of the polyp these are arranged in eight longitudinal tracts, but do not form a collaret or points. The surface of the colony base has similar spindles, 
<quantity box="[713,879,2012,2036]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="21" pageNumber="472" unit="mm" value="0.105" valueMax="0.13" valueMin="0.08">0.08–0.13 mm</quantity>
long, with longer, simple tubercles and spinose projections (
<figureCitation box="[291,388,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,587,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,587,1753]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Leptophyton benayahui, RMNH Coel.40209 (SAF333). a, tentaclesclerites; b, sclerites from proximal region of polyps and colony surface; c, sclerites from base of colony." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1114557/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Fig. 12c</figureCitation>
). The general shapes and sizes of these sclerites are similar to those depicted for the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,151,176]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">holotype</typeStatus>
(Ofwegen and Schleyer 1997: 
<figureCitation box="[498,577,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1910,1932]" captionTargetBox="[190,1384,193,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[190,1384,193,1878]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. a, b: Lampophyton spinatum n. sp., holotype, RMNH Coel. 40198 (SAF164); b, close-up of polyparium surface and margin of stalk; c-e: Lampophyton spinatum n. sp., SAF125; d, lateral view of polyparium surface; e, top view of polyparium;f, g:Lampophyton planiceps RMNH Coel.40200 (SAF237),lateral view of polyparium and margin of stalk; g,top view of partially retracted polyparium.s = sclerites protruding through colony surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1114499/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[591,607,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1658,1680]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1637]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,1637]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE4. Lampophyton spinatum n. sp., holotype,RMNH Coel.40198 (SAF164).a, scleritesfrom upperregion ofstalk and polyparium; b, tuberculate spindles and needles from base of stalk; c, smooth spindles from base of stalk; d, details of tubercular ornamentation:top and middle, spindles of upper surface of stalk; bottom, spindles of base of stalk." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1114507/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">4</figureCitation>
), but the details of the tubercular and spinose ornamentation can be seen more clearly in our material. The interior of the colony lacks sclerites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,151,285]" box="[199,1295,260,285]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">
Spherical gametes, 
<quantity box="[417,566,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" unit="mm" value="0.475" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.35">0.35–0.6 mm</quantity>
in diameter, can be seen within the stalk of 
<collectionCode box="[1059,1143,261,284]" country="Netherlands" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" name="National Museum of Natural History, Naturalis" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">RMNH</collectionCode>
Coel. 40210.
</paragraph>
